# Work tracking (GitHub)

Uses **GitHub Issues** + **ArrDash** project board — see [docs/github-workflow.md](../docs/github-workflow.md).

**Authority:** `main` on https://github.com/Unthred/ArrDash is the source of truth. Live deploy on Unraid is built from that tree (or local checkout of `main`).

## Issues (required)

- Create an issue **before code** unless the user explicitly says docs-only / typo / chore with no tracking needed.
- **Always** use `scripts/arrdash-issue-create.sh` (repo issue + project board card). Do **not** use bare `gh issue create`.
- Move card status as work progresses: Todo → In Progress → Done.
- Chat is not the system of record — **issues**, **PRs**, and **docs/** are.

## Branches

- **`main`** — integration; deploy from here after merge.
- **Feature branches** (preferred): `feature/issue-<id>-short-name` off `main`, PR back to **`main`**.

## Commits and PRs

- Commits tied to an issue: prefix with `#<id>:` (example: `#12: Compact status bar tooltips`).
- PR body includes `Closes #<id>`.
- Update **CHANGELOG.md** and relevant **docs/** in the same PR when behaviour or config changes.
- Do not push secrets (`docker-compose.yml` with keys stays gitignored).

## Agents

1. Confirm or create issue on the board.
2. Implement on a feature branch (or user-directed branch).
3. Run `dotnet test tests/ArrDash.Tests/ArrDash.Tests.csproj` for logic/settings changes.
4. Open PR with template checklist filled in.
5. After merge: user rebuilds container (`docker compose build && docker compose up -d`) unless CI exists.

